        </tbody>
    </table>
</div>
</p>
<p>This builds the exact same DQL query we had before. Because we're inside
of the <code>CategoryRepository</code>, the <code>createQueryBuilder()</code> function automatically
configures itself to select from the <code>Category</code> entity, using <code>cat</code> as the
alias.</p>
<p>To get a <code>Query</code> object from this, say <code>$qb-&gt;getQuery()</code>:</p>
<p><div class="code-block-wrapper" data-code-block-guid="49ad83d6ba">
    <div class="meta">
        <div class="actions">
