<p>Refresh! Look closely:</p>
<pre><code>SELECT cat FROM AppBundle\Entity\Category cat ORDER BY cat.name DESC</code></pre>
<p>That's character-by-character the <em>exact</em> same DQL that we wrote before.
So the query builder is just a <em>nice</em> way to help write DQL, and I prefer
it because I get method auto-completion and it can help you re-use pieces
of a query, like a complex JOIN, across multiple queries. I'll show you
that later.</p>
<p>Remove the <code>die</code> statement and refresh to make sure it's working:</p>
