	                        <div id="dsq-comment-message-3001910357" class="dsq-comment-message">
	                            <div id="dsq-comment-text-3001910357" class="dsq-comment-text">
	                                <p>Ah I see.. So this alias is arbitrary and it's set for the first time when you call "createQueryBuilder()" if you use Doctrine query builder, e.g. "$this-&gt;createQueryBuilder('cat')", where `cat` is the alias of table for Category entity (because you're calling this method from CategoryRepository). If you use DQL, you'll need to specify alias right after the table name like "SELECT cat FROM AppBundle\Entity\Category AS cat". Does it answer your question?</p><p>Cheers!</p>
	                            </div>
	                        </div>
