	                                <p>Hey Hakim,</p><p>Actually, it's a core SQL feature, you can use `AS` keyword to make alias for table or field, but also you can omit it. Check the wiki page about SQL aliases: <a href="https://disq.us/url?url=https%3A%2F%2Fen.wikipedia.org%2Fwiki%2FAlias_%28SQL%29%3AiKhfOiqyPpdT7Q4R3QF9MB-Py00&amp;cuid=1175718" rel="nofollow noopener">https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/...</a></p><p>Cheers!</p>
